%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d1d62931ab01cd14b84145ae3bdd017f, type: 3}
  m_Name: Chapter 3
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  chapter: 3
  levelTerms:
  - level: 11
    terms:
    - term: Law of Inertia
      unit: 
      type: 0
      description: An object remain in current state unless acted by outside/unbalanced
        force.
      details: "Newton\u2019s First Law, the Law of Inertia, states that an object
        will remain in its current state unless there is a change in its equilibrium
        caused by an unbalanced, outside force."
    - term: Law of Acceleration
      unit: 
      type: 0
      description: The object accelerates if an unbalanced net force is applied.
      details: "The object is said to be moving when it's accelerating In Newton\u2019s
        Second Law, which represents the aftermath of an object exposed to unbalanced
        forces, states that an object is said to be moving when it is accelerating. "
    - term: Law of Interaction
      unit: 
      type: 0
      description: There is always an equal and opposing amount of force counteracting
        another force.
      details: "The premise of this Law is simple: there is always an equal \u2013and
        opposing \u2013 amount of force counteracting against another force. In context,
        the Third Law explains the First and Second Laws. An example of this would
        be Normal force (FN). In it, the normal force is always paired with weight
        (FW), which is normal force\u2019s polar opposite. The two force, when paired
        together, are called interaction force-pairs."
    - term: Inertia
      unit: 
      type: 1
      description: It is resistance of an object to change its state of motion
      details: 'Simply put, if acceleration is absent (ex: a = 0 m/s <sup>2</sup>)the
        object is in a state of rest.'
  - level: 13
    terms:
    - term: Force
      unit: F
      type: 2
      description: It is the influence that tends to change an object's state of
        motion.
      details: "The force unit is Newtons (N). 1 N = 1 kg \xD7 m/s\xB2.\n\nFormula:\nF
        = ma\n\nF = force\nm = mass\na = acceleration"
    - term: Weight
      unit: F<sub>W</sub>
      type: 2
      description: It is the force exerted by gravity on the object (going down).
      details: 'Formula:

        F<sub>W</sub> = mg


        F<sub>W</sub> = weight
        force

        m = mass

        g = gravity'
    - term: Friction
      unit: F<sub>n</sub>
      type: 2
      description: Resistance of surface or object acting upon another object on
        contact (going left).
      details: "Formula:\nF<sub>f</sub> = u \xD7 F<sub>N</sub>\n\nF<sub>f</sub> =
        friction\nu = coefficient of friction\r\nF<sub>N</sub> = normal force"
    - term: Net Force
      unit: F<sub>n</sub>
      type: 2
      description: It is the sum of all forces acting on an object
      details: 'Formula:

        F<sub>net</sub> = F<sub>A</sub> + F<sub>B</sub>


        F<sub>A</sub>,
        F<sub>B</sub>, F<sub>C</sub>, etc... is arbitrary.

        Net force is
        the sum of all different forces acting on an object. '
